how can my cgi script read and write to files and directories outside the cgi bin directory stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how can my cgi script read and write to files and directories outside the cgi bin directory categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how can my cgi script read and write to files and directories outside the cgi bin directory search this site you need to assign afs read or write permissions for the cgi principal to the directory that the cgi script is working with see setting permissions for information on how to set afs permissions generally your cgi principal is your username followed by the cgi suffix you should be able to see your cgi principal name when you list the access control list of your cgi bin directory by running fs listacl also you will need to give the cgi principal list privileges to all the parent directories of the working directory cgi stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
